The paper proposes an IDE-based web search solution for programming problems, which involves collecting data from web search APIs and a programming Q&A site. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the traditional web search experience by taking into account the context of programming problems, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) aspects. The paper also mentions that the proposed approach considers the content of the selected error, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of web search APIs and a programming Q&A site, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category as well.
